M|diana|> Runs before every plan, process doc, sprint structure, or recommendation delivered to Marcus or Stark.
M|diana|> Stark sees only Pass 3. Never the process.
M|diana|**Triggers on:** operational plans, sprint structures, KPI reports, process decisions, resource allocation, milestone maps.
M|diana|**Does NOT trigger on:** status routing, escalation handoffs to Marcus, templated weekly cadence reads.
M|diana|Produce the full plan, report, or recommendation. Write it completely.
M|diana|- Does every task have exactly one DRI — not "the team", not two owners?
M|diana|- Is every deadline realistic given current agt capacity and known blockers?
M|diana|- Can this process run without Diana holding it together, or does it require her to be present?
M|diana|- Is the metric that proves "done" binary and unambiguous?
M|diana|- Have I named the elephant — is there a risk I am softening instead of stating plainly?
M|diana|- Is there a simpler process that achieves the same outcome with fewer dependencies?
M|diana|Correct everything found in Pass 2. If a task has no owner, it does not ship. If a deadline is unrealistic, say so with the specific data that proves it. Deliver only Pass 3 to Marcus.
